		<a name="58438"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/12/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 20:06:35</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=135"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=135')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=58438&amp;TOPIC_ID=7098&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=EoT+vs+high+level+mage+pet+parses&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         First of all, the EoT was NOT FOCUSED.  It was hitting for 69 instead of 73.  Thats probably good, if the EoT won, the nerf parade would have started. </P><P> Also, I could put a damage shield on a tree stump and it would beat a pet.  Whats the point of damage shielding a pet in pet to pet duels?  DS is a SPELL YOU CAST.  Do we cast any spells on our pets besides the obvious haste?  I know the epic has an inate DS, but why bother dueling if a DS is involved? </P><P> EoT would have to do 3500 damage or whatever the Epic pet has for hps.  Now say it averages 35 a hit, it needs to hit the epic 100 times to kill it.  With a 33 point DS, that is 3300 damage to the EoT, WAY more hps then it has.  So you could just hit /pet back off and the epic would still win if it had a DS on it.  Its a stupid comparison of pet power.  The DS does all the work and the pets real offense/defense skills mean little.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

